The paper deals with the study of configuration spaces of 1-dof linkages in 2D, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The focus is on the algebraic complexity of describing endpoints of intervals in the Cayley configuration space, which involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic techniques (cs.DM, cs.GT). The paper also discusses planarity and forbidden minor characterizations, which are topics in systems and control theory (cs.SY).
